commitResults.messageBody:
Current implementation shows success message when adding information
to alternative contact fields which already exists.

This is a bug as any updates to information should be done through
another command edit.

Current implementation does not allow to edit the alternative
contact information of a person.

Relevant changes are made so that these fields can be edited.

commitResults.messageTitle: Remove unnecessary code and improve addalt implementation
commitResults.messageBody:
There are some unused methods in AddAltCommand class.

Moreover, the string pattern in Linkedin and Telegram class enables the
acceptance of weird values.

To reduce clutter, code not needed is removed and the VALIDATION_REGEX
is changed to simulate like the real world for Linkedin and Telegram.

Currently, edit fails even though an attribute of Person is present and
user likes to change to another value.

The equals method of Person is not updated accordingly; it does not

maintain code coverage.

if they are not edited in the edit command.

Also, edit command allows storing the same primary and secondary email.

command.

Code is shortened by utilizing in built functions from java docs.
